                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways, Inc./698:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-28T09:00:00-04:30"
                            >October 28, 1929—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>174. Legation’s 173, October 27, 8 p.m.; and despatch No. 1996, September
                        29th.<note n="46" xml:id="d439fn46">Neither printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>[Paraphrase.] The Pan American Airways should be advised to press their proposal
                    actively before the French service is established. The situation is now
                    favorable to Pan American Airways but it may change later. [End paraphrase.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
